Hackipedia.org TODO list:

- Core code
  - ANSI escape sequence parsing
  - state machine
  - bit rate counter (for code to pace itself at a commom modem baud rate i.e. 9600)
  - structure to represent terminal "screen"
    - characters are 32-bit each (for unicode representation of source i.e. CP437 to UTF-8, or UTF-8 ANSIs)
    - attributes
      - color (background, foreground)
      - bright/dim
      - blink
      - double width/height
      - 88-color palette
      - 256-color palette
      - 24-bit truecolor
    - scrollback buffer
    - cursor position, visibility, color, form (line, block?)
- Requirements
  - Standard C I/O
  - GNU libiconv (compile-time table generation)
  - fontconfig
  - freetype
  - libpng
  - libgif
- General testing
  - SDL app to "play" an ANSI animation
- ANSI graphics (non-moving ANSI)
  - convert to PNG
  - convert to HTML
- ANSI animations (moving ANSI)
  - convert to GIF
- Web browser display (for moving ANSI)
  - HTML5 ANSI player (JavaScript + Canvas implementation)

